The Global Citizen Festival, which was launched in 2012, is a continuation of the Global Poverty Project, an international public organization that hopes to eradicate poverty by increasing the number of people who will actively fight it.
To get a free ticket for the event (unless you want to pay for the VIP ticket), visitors must perform a number of tasks or "acts", such as taking part in a volunteer project, write an email to the world leader, make a phone call or anything else to help draw attention to the organization's goal - eradicating poverty.
