Speaking to the United Nations General Assembly, Foreign Minister Walid al-Mualem said conditions in the country were improving.
“Today, the real situation has become more stable and safer due to the progress made in the fight against terrorism,” he said.
The government continues to restore terrorist-torn areas so that people can return to normal life.
All conditions have been created for the voluntary return of refugees to a country they had to leave due to terrorism, as well as unilateral economic measures that influenced their daily lives and limited their livelihoods.
The UN estimates that more than 5.5 million Syrians have fled the country since the beginning of the war in 2011.
Another six million people still living in the country need humanitarian assistance.
Al-Mualem said the Syrian government would gladly accept assistance in restoring the war-torn country.
But he stressed that they will not accept conditional assistance or assistance from countries that support the riot.
